comments.body:
Carpenter ants are on the decline due to the rapidly shifting job market, I love the creative suggestion but would caution against unfavourable changes.

https://www.usatoday.com/story/money/business/2013/08/30/disappearing-jobs-in-usa/2750105/

See rank 2.

It's too late. We already took it upon the organization (typesofants.com coming soon) to document the various professions. Carpenter ant, while as a species is on the decline, is gaining in popularity as a profession.

There is also a lack of crazy yellow ants. The job market for them is on the rise 

https://www.commentary.org/articles/pascal-emmanuel-gobry/yellow-rise-paris/
